The Kubernetes Management MCP Server provides comprehensive cluster management capabilities, enabling deployment automation, resource monitoring, and container orchestration through Claude.

## Core Capabilities

### Cluster Management
- Node status and resource monitoring
- Namespace management and isolation
- RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration
- Network policy management
- Storage class and persistent volume operations

### Workload Management
- **Deployments**: Application lifecycle management
- **StatefulSets**: Stateful application orchestration
- **DaemonSets**: Node-level service deployment
- **Jobs & CronJobs**: Batch processing and scheduled tasks
- **Pods**: Direct container management

### Service & Networking
- Service discovery and load balancing
- Ingress controller configuration
- ConfigMap and Secret management
- Network policy enforcement
- Service mesh integration

### Scaling & Resource Management
- Horizontal Pod Autoscaling (HPA)
- Vertical Pod Autoscaling (VPA)
- Cluster autoscaling
- Resource quotas and limits
- Quality of Service (QoS) management

### Monitoring & Observability
- Pod and container metrics
- Event tracking and alerting
- Log aggregation and analysis
- Health checks and readiness probes
- Performance monitoring

